steps.description:
Thanks for logging this @muety!

Just to bring the goal into view, the v1 prometheus module had the ability to set a value to be used by the `host` label, which effectively solved the cardinality problem (i.e. the fact that there isn't a bounded set of values that can be used if it's determined auto
```yaml
example.org {
    root /var/www/html
    file_server
    metrics /metrics {
        host "example.org"
    }
}
```

codeSnippets:
example.com {
  respond /foo "hello world"
}
example2.com {
  respond /bar "hello world"
}
example2.com:8443 {
  respond /baz "hello world"
}
